Title: Providing 64 Nos. ladders for Expansion joints, manholes and air vents of penstocks 1 to 10 along the hill slope of Sharavathy Generating Station, KPCL, Jogfalls 577435, Shimoga Dist, Karnataka
Location: KPCL Executive Engineer Turbine Office SVP Jog
Description: Supply, fabrication, transportation, hoisting, shifting and erection of expansion joint manholes and air vents steel ladders to penstocks situated at hill slope area of Sharavathy Generating Station. The supplied structural materials will be good quality with quantity and as per Indian standards and Technical specifications. Providing scaffolding material for dismantling old structures and erection of new ladders. Dismantling of existing old structural steel ladders, sorting the dismantled material, disposal of unserviceable material and stacking the serviceable material as directed by the Engineer in charge at site. Fabrication and erection of new ladders and platforms to penstock expansion joints using MS structural steel of required items specification and sizes. Providing two coats of painting after one coat of primer to structural steel surfaces with epoxy paint of approve quality. Welding, gas cutting, drilling holes, transporting, hoisting, lowering, fixing are covered with scope of work and contractor should arrange for the required equipment, lifting tools, tackles, ropes, spanners and safety gadgets and insurance for the laborers technicians deployed for the works.

Title: Reconditioning of existing LTAC Panel at 66/11KV Switchyard control room at Shiva HES
Location: KPCL Executive Engineer EMO Office SVP ShivanaSamudram
Description: At 66/11KV Switchyard, Shivasamudram, 11kV bus is provided on the 11kV side of 6.3MVA , 66/11kV Transformer, 1 No. 11kV Bank Breaker (Incomer) is provided and thereon it is extended to the 3 No. 11KV Feeders viz. F1, F2 & F3. Two No. Auxiliary transformers are provided at the 66/11KV Switchyard for the auxiliary power supply needs of the Control Room in the ODY. One No. will be in service and the other one will be maintained as standby. The 11KV power supply to the auxiliary transformers is tapped from the 11KV Bus provided in the 66/11KV Switchyard. LTAC panels (Section 1 & 2) have been provided in the switchyard control room for catering the 415V/230V power supply needs of various equipments like Battery chargers, ACDBs in the yard, etc. The LTAC panels were commissioned long back during the VVNL period.
